definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as tetradecanoyl (myristoyl) and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl) and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (9Z)-octadec-9-enoyl (oleoyl) and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z-icosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol.
A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-hexadecanoyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol.
A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol.
A 1-hexadecanoyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and octadecanoyl (stearoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z-octadecenoyl (oleoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of (10E,12Z)-octadecadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 9.
An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of 10E,12E-octadecadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 9.
An oxoeicosadienoic acid that consists of 11Z,13E-oxoeicosadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 15.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecanoyl (stearoyl) and 9Z-octadecenoyl (oleoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
An oxo fatty acid that is obtained by oxidation of the allylic hydroxy of any  hydroxyeicosadienoic acid during its metabolism.

A hydroxyeicosadienoic acid that consists of 11Z,13E-eicosatrienoic acid bearing a 15-hydroxy substituent. It is produced by non-enzymatic oxidation of 11,14-eicosadienoic acid. There are no reports in the literature of biological activity associated with 15-HEDE.
A hydroxy fatty acid that is any icosadienoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent. An oxidation product of icosadienoic acid metabolism.
An oxaspiro compound that is (25R)-5alpha-spirostan substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3 and 6 (the 2alpha,3beta,6beta stereoisomer).
A 20-carbon, polyunsaturated fatty acid having two double bonds at unspecified positions.
An epoxy fatty acid obtained by formal epoxidation of one of the double bonds of any icosapentaenoic acid.
An EpETE obtained by formal epoxidation of the 17,18-double bond of all-cis-5,8,11,14,17-icosapentaenoic acid.
An EC 1.13.11.* (oxidoreductase acting on single donors and incorporating 2 atoms of oxygen) inhibitor that interferes with the action of indoleamine 2,3-dioxygenase (EC 1.13.11.52).
An EpDPE obtained by formal epoxidation of the 16,17-double bond of docosa-4,7,10,13,16,19-hexaenoic acid.
A hydroxyeicosatrienoic acid that consists of 6E,8Z,11Z-eicosatrienoic acid bearing a 5-hydroxy substituent.
A 1-acyl-2-octadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl); major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-2-tetradecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl); major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-2-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1-acyl group is also hexadecanoyl; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatetraenoyl (arachidonoyl) respectively; major species at pH 7.3.
A 5,8,11-eicosatrienoic acid in which all three double bonds adopt cis-configuration.
A hydroxyeicosatrienoic acid that consists of 9E,11Z,14Z-eicosatrienoic acid bearing an 8-hydroxy substituent.
A DiHETE that consists of 6E,8Z,11Z,13E-icosatetraenoic acid having the two hydroxy groups located at positions 5 and 15.
A hydroxy fatty acid that is any eicosatetraenoic acid bearing two hydroxy substituents.
